Gently wrapping baby securely in a receiving baby blanket with only their head peeking out. Swaddling is safe for newborns as their body is safely snug inside the muslin swaddle and makes baby feels like he/she is still inside the womb.

Light weight, and breathable material either a bamboo swaddling blanket or cotton swaddle blanket works best for swaddling.

Swaddling helps to calm a newborn baby and improve sleep. Most babies will sleep more soundly when swaddled than left with their arms out. It also helps reduce the risk of moro reflex which can startle a newborn and wake them up.

Gently wrapping baby securely in a receiving baby blanket with only their head peeking out. Swaddling is safe for newborns as their body is safely snug inside the muslin swaddle and makes baby feels like he/she is still inside the womb.

Light weight, and breathable material either a bamboo swaddling blanket or cotton swaddle blanket works best for swaddling.

Swaddling helps to calm a newborn baby and improve sleep. Most babies will sleep more soundly when swaddled than left with their arms out. It also helps reduce the risk of moro reflex which can startle a newborn and wake them up.

Gently wrapping baby securely in a receiving baby blanket with only their head peeking out. Swaddling is safe for newborns as their body is safely snug inside the muslin swaddle and makes baby feels like he/she is still inside the womb.
What blanket is best for swaddling?
Light weight, and breathable material either a bamboo swaddling blanket or cotton swaddle blanket works best for swaddling.
Do babies sleep better when swaddled?
Swaddling helps to calm a newborn baby and improve sleep. Most babies will sleep more soundly when swaddled than left with their arms out. It also helps reduce the risk of moro reflex which can startle a newborn and wake them up.
